sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Cmd as Existing command entry point
    participant WF as Workflow orchestration
    participant Reg as Existing registry
    participant LC as Existing lifecycle
    participant Ren as Static renderer
    participant State as Lifecycle state
    participant Lock as Workspace mutation lock
    participant T as Registered target
    participant Ev as Evidence
    participant Gate as DPA-500 gates

    User->>Cmd: request governed refresh
    Cmd->>WF: preserve governed command behavior
    WF->>LC: request refresh
    LC->>State: recover or abandon interrupted prior instance
    LC->>Reg: resolve and validate projection + partition contracts
    Reg-->>LC: validated declarative contracts
    LC->>Ren: render exactly one target payload
    Ren-->>LC: text or bytes only
    LC-->>WF: immutable dry-run plan + identity
    WF->>LC: execute exact plan
    LC->>LC: Preflight all guards
    LC->>Lock: acquire local mutation lock
    LC->>Reg: revalidate contracts under lock
    LC->>State: revalidate accepted state and interruption status
    LC->>T: atomically replace complete target
    LC-->>WF: written-unverified
    LC->>T: reread and verify complete bytes
    LC->>State: persist verification / acceptance-state candidate data
    LC->>Ev: emit bounded non-authoritative evidence
    LC->>Lock: release
    WF->>Gate: request acceptance evaluation
    Gate-->>State: accepted or remain non-accepted

    Note over Cmd,T: For CURRENT_HANDOFF, adapt every then-known writer; DISC-003b confirms admin-refresh-pr as an observed writer and chat-switch-complete as not writing the target at the recorded ref.
